Interface ResponseProcessor<RESPONSE_TYPE>

  • Type Parameters:
    RESPONSE_TYPE - The type of response.
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Transport<RESPONSE_TYPE>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BoundResponseProcessor, Request.CallResponseProcessor, ResponseCounter, SignalResponseProcessor

    public interface ResponseProcessor<RESPONSE_TYPE>
    A ResponseProcessor is an application callback to handle the response from a request.

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void processResponse(RESPONSE_TYPE response)
      The processResponse method accepts the response of a request.

    • Method Detail

      • processResponse

        void processResponse(RESPONSE_TYPE response)
                     throws java.lang.Exception
        The processResponse method accepts the response of a request.

        This method need not be thread-safe, as it is always invoked from the same light-weight thread (mailbox) that passed the Request and ResponseProcessor objects.

        Parameters:
        response - The response to a request.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception
